    "content": "<p>Three concentric metallic shells A, B and C of radii a, b and c (a &lt; b &lt; c) have surface charge densities +$$\\sigma$$, $$-$$$$\\sigma$$ and +$$\\sigma$$ respectively. The potential of shell B is</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l2ns7ka9/49a74e73-b563-4b6b-84ba-28ea4a89ffeb/659a1e10-c992-11ec-bcc9-bb19dc2f1da9/file-1l2ns7kaa.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l2ns7ka9/49a74e73-b563-4b6b-84ba-28ea4a89ffeb/659a1e10-c992-11ec-bcc9-bb19dc2f1da9/file-1l2ns7kaa.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"WB JEE 2022 Physics - Capacitor Question 6 English\"></p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "$$(a + b + c){\\sigma  \\over {{\\varepsilon _0}}}$$"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "$${{\\sigma c} \\over {{\\varepsilon _0}}}$$"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "$$\\left( {{{{a^2}} \\over c} - {{{b^2}} \\over c} + c} \\right){\\sigma  \\over {{\\varepsilon _0}}}$$"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "$$\\left( {{{{a^2}} \\over c} - b + c} \\right){\\sigma  \\over {{\\varepsilon _0}}}$$"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "D"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Net potential at any point $$(r = b)$$ of shell B</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l8d7ck9w/45b08605-3f26-43c9-b4a5-edba70fd9802/46b50640-3a8a-11ed-9bbd-a30f36b056fe/file-1l8d7ck9x.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l8d7ck9w/45b08605-3f26-43c9-b4a5-edba70fd9802/46b50640-3a8a-11ed-9bbd-a30f36b056fe/file-1l8d7ck9x.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"WB JEE 2022 Physics - Capacitor Question 6 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>= potential due to shell A + potential due to shell B + potential due to shell C.</p>\n<p>$$V = {V_{A,\\,out}} + {V_{B,\\,surface}} + {V_{C,\\,in}}$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {V_{A,\\,out}} + {V_{B,\\,surface}} + {V_{C,\\,surface}}$$ (for shell, $${V_{in}} = {V_{surface}}$$)</p>\n<p>$$V = {1 \\over {4\\pi {\\varepsilon _0}}}\\left[ {{{{q_a}} \\over b} + {{{q_b}} \\over b} + {{{q_c}} \\over c}} \\right]$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {1 \\over {4\\pi {\\varepsilon _0}}}\\left[ {{{\\sigma 4\\pi {a^2}} \\over b} + {{( - \\sigma )4\\pi {b^2}} \\over b} + {{(\\sigma )4\\pi {c^2}} \\over c}} \\right]$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {\\sigma  \\over {{\\varepsilon _0}}}\\left[ {{{{a^2}} \\over b} - b + c} \\right]$$</p>",
