    "explanation": "$${1 \\over C} = {1 \\over {{C_1}}} + {1 \\over {{C_2}}} = {1 \\over 4} + {1 \\over 4} = {2 \\over 4}$$<br><br>C = 2$$\\mu F$$<br><br>2$$\\mu F$$ will be parallel to 4$$\\mu F$$, so the resultant capacitance<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m5akkfwk/4204938a-3aae-4dbe-bc87-4c7adec5453e/c209f440-c66a-11ef-95a8-2787fde10bdd/file-jaoe38c1m5akkfwl.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m5akkfwk/4204938a-3aae-4dbe-bc87-4c7adec5453e/c209f440-c66a-11ef-95a8-2787fde10bdd/file-jaoe38c1m5akkfwl.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"WB JEE 2016 Physics - Capacitor Question 10 English Explanation 1\"><br><br>$$C' = {C_1} + {C_2} = 2\\mu F + 4\\mu F$$<br><br>$$ = 6\\mu F$$<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m5akkdfh/fa6ce358-825f-4366-ad36-461c699bd9d5/c0209ad0-c66a-11ef-95a8-2787fde10bdd/file-jaoe38c1m5akkdfi.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m5akkdfh/fa6ce358-825f-4366-ad36-461c699bd9d5/c0209ad0-c66a-11ef-95a8-2787fde10bdd/file-jaoe38c1m5akkdfi.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"WB JEE 2016 Physics - Capacitor Question 10 English Explanation 2\"><br><br>$${1 \\over {{C^{''}}}} = {1 \\over {4\\mu F}} + {1 \\over {4\\mu F}} = {2 \\over 4}\\mu F$$<br><br>$$C'' = 2\\mu F$$<br><br>$$ \\therefore $$ $${C_{AB}} = 2\\mu F + 6\\mu F$$<br><br>$$ = 8\\mu F$$",
