    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lh5qifr3/e23b6bbe-34f3-40e1-992e-d2e48e9d1ba6/e4bcbcf0-e89c-11ed-a420-0d214ea4e520/file-1lh5qifr4.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lh5qifr3/e23b6bbe-34f3-40e1-992e-d2e48e9d1ba6/e4bcbcf0-e89c-11ed-a420-0d214ea4e520/file-1lh5qifr4.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"WB JEE 2023 Physics - Capacitor Question 4 English\"></p>\n<p>The figure shows two identical parallel plate capacitors A and B of capacitances C connected to a battery. The key K is initially closed. The switch is now opened and the free spaces between the plates of the capacitors are filled with a dielectric constant 3. Then which of the following statements is/are true?</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "When the switch is closed, total energy stored in the two capacitors is CV$$^2$$."
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "When the switch is opened, no charge is stored in the capacitor B."
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "When the switch is opened, energy stored in capacitor B is $$\\frac{3}{2}$$CV$$^2$$."
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "When the switch is opened, total energy stored in two capacitors is $$\\frac{5}{3}$$CV$$^2$$."
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A",
      "D"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1lrii1mwf/56f6a694-30cf-40d4-a7b8-c512f3e81328/22b3abf0-b59c-11ee-88fe-93f7151820af/file-6y3zli1lrii1mwg.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1lrii1mwf/56f6a694-30cf-40d4-a7b8-c512f3e81328/22b3abf0-b59c-11ee-88fe-93f7151820af/file-6y3zli1lrii1mwg.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"WB JEE 2023 Physics - Capacitor Question 4 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>Initially switch $$K$$ is closed,</p>\n<p>Energy stored in capacitor $$A, E_A=\\frac{1}{2} C V^2$$</p>\n<p>Energy stored in capacitor $$B, E_B=\\frac{1}{2} C V^2$$</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ Total energy stored in two capacitors,</p>\n<p>$$E_i=E_A+E_B=\\frac{1}{2} C V^2+\\frac{1}{2} C V^2=C V^2$$</p>\n<p>When switch $$K$$ is open, and a dielectric $$(K=3)$$ is inserted in both capacitors, then</p>\n<p>Energy stored in capacitor $$A$$,</p>\n<p>$$E_A=\\frac{1}{2}(3 C) V^2=\\frac{3}{2} C V^2$$</p>\n<p>Energy stored in capacitor B,</p>\n<p>$$E_p=\\frac{(C V)^2}{2 \\times 3 C}=\\frac{1}{6} C V^2$$</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ Total energy stored in two capacitors,</p>\n<p>$$E_f=E_A+E_B=\\left(\\frac{3}{2}+\\frac{1}{6}\\right) C V^2=\\frac{5}{3} C V^2$$</p>",
